- I believe that parents - not the government - must be the party ultimately responsible for the quality of children's education.
- I believe that to guarantee the continued freedom and prosperity of our nation, we must prioritize space exploration and its subsequent economy.

- I believe in all First Amendment rights, plus a right to privacy.
- I believe in the 2nd Amendment and the right of law-abiding citizens to bear arms.
- I believe in the absolute sovereignty of every individual. This includes protecting the individual's medical rights.
I have many views that people would consider 'Democrat' and many that are 'Republican'.

-We live in a Constitutional Republic
-Our gov't has a republican structure, giving our gov't responsibilities clearly defined & limited by the Constitution.
-This is our form of gov't & I believe it's our best guarantor of a free & prosperous society. This makes me a republican.
When people ask me what I mean when I say I'm a "small r Republican", here's what I say:

Anyone who has served & interacted with the VA knows that it is chronically under-resourced.

America remains the land of opportunity. But for how much longer? Our leaders dismiss the problems of working Americans, ignore rising prices, & crush businesses w/higher taxes & nonsensical regulations. We need leaders who understand the challenges that most Americans deal with.
At 4:05pm I'll be chatting with @SteveJaxonDrive on KSRO 103.5 FM.

Schools are the beneficiaries of well-rounded students. Businesses are the beneficiaries of well-rounded, educated citizens. Economies & societies are the beneficiaries of well-rounded, educated, & capable citizens. It is time we aligned our educational system accordingly.
Before we can make progress on anything else, our leaders must prioritize the economy. Do not kill the goose that lays the golden egg.

Thanks to our wealth and innovation, we have have the resources to build the greatest educational system in the world.
Thanks to our wealth and innovation, we have the technology to fuel our daily lives with renewable energy.

Hardest to ignore, prices of basic goods are at a 40 yr high & America lost over 100,000 businesses in the last 2 yrs. Yet, in spite of our politicians' best efforts, the U.S. economy remains a symbol of opportunity, & the greatest wealth-generating machine the world has seen.

It took a pandemic & lockdown to reveal how badly our leaders have damaged the foundation of the U.S. economy. They exported our manufacturing base to China, endangering our supply chain & nat'l security. They weaken the dollar & threaten its place as the global trade currency.

Total economic growth is the foundation on which all progress depends.
Career politicians forgot that long ago, and now we careen towards continued economic decline.
